    "type": "VerificationActivity",
    "name": "Mesh Independence Verification Study",
    "description": "A three-level mesh refinement study was conducted on the FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry to establish mesh-independent hemolysis index predictions. Coarse (2.1M cells), medium (6.4M cells), and fine (14.7M cells) meshes were generated using ANSYS ICEM; the Richardson extrapolation method was applied to quantify discretization error. The study confirmed that the medium mesh yields a grid convergence index below 3% for the primary hemolysis quantity of interest at all five operating points. Results were reviewed by the lead CFD analyst and documented in the internal verification log.",
    "activityType": "MeshRefinementStudy",
